<dl id="s14036l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14036l">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s14all.htm#s14036l">sector 36(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> opium &#62;/&#60; wine</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Coleridge, professing to believe (without reason assigned) that <mark>opium-eating</mark> is criminal, and in some mysterious sense <mark>more criminal than wine-drinking</mark> or porter-drinking, having therefore the strongest <i>moral</i> motive for abstaining from it <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <small> Thomas De Quincey, <a name="TDQC" href="/udra/udex.htm#tdqc"><cite title="source">Confessions of an English Opium-Eater</cite></a> (1909), 19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
